column7: Aquatic phase with keeled tail. Yellow green with red spots. Looks gravid.
Becoming olive colored especially on the ventral side.
Darkish no spots, bright orange belly with dark spots.
Dead (appears to have been partially eaten by the short tailed shrew)
Dead in bucket (same bucket as dead dusky [cataloged in separate record] ).
Dead, tail missing (in the same bucket as the shrew).
dead; dried up in snake trap
Very cold or dead, tail broken.
Spots on head and tip of tail are orange.
Left front toes are shorter than those on the right.
Left forefoot has toes missing. (Found in the same trap as the woodland and meadow mice.
Not dead, but not very lively
Yellow flecking on back and sides, no larger yellow spots
strong markings and very orange under legs
Outer finger/digit on foreleg twisted backward and wrapped around next finger, injury or mutation?
Only one leg. Doesn’t look like it was eaten or damaged. No scar. Natural.
Left hind leg missing toes, only club like foot. Mutation.
Left front leg ends at MST. Well healed stump or mutation.
Very dark. Hard to see a mask on its face. We thought at first it was a green frog.
dead; dried up in snake trap
dead - appeared to have gotten caught in collar - full of water
Very pale, appeared dead but still breathing slightly.
unusual bilateral dark markings on back of head (sketch on data sheet)
some small black patches on sides
